========================
CODE SNIPPETS
========================
TITLE: Remove useAssistant Hook from AI SDK
DESCRIPTION: The `useAssistant` hook has been entirely removed from the AI SDK. For assistant-like functionality, users are advised to leverage the `useChat` hook with appropriate configurations, potentially following external examples.

SOURCE: https://github.com/vercel/ai/blob/main/content/docs/08-migration-guides/26-migration-guide-5-0.mdx#_snippet_42

LANGUAGE: TypeScript
CODE:
```
import { useAssistant } from '@ai-sdk/react';
```

LANGUAGE: TypeScript
CODE:
```
// useAssistant has been removed
// Use useChat with appropriate configuration instead
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Vercel AI SDK useChat Hook Parameters
DESCRIPTION: This documentation outlines the various parameters that can be passed to the `useChat` hook in the Vercel AI SDK. These parameters allow for customization of API endpoints, initial states, message handling, error handling, and other advanced features for building AI chat applications.

SOURCE: https://github.com/vercel/ai/blob/v5/content/docs/07-reference/02-ai-sdk-ui/01-use-chat.mdx#_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: APIDOC
CODE:
```
Parameter: api
  Type: string = '/api/chat'
  Optional: true
  Description: The API endpoint that is called to generate chat responses. It can be a relative path (starting with '/') or an absolute URL.

Parameter: id
  Type: string
  Optional: true
  Description: An unique identifier for the chat. If not provided, a random one will be generated. When provided, the `useChat` hook with the same `id` will have shared states across components. This is useful when you have multiple components showing the same chat stream.

Parameter: initialInput
  Type: string = ''
  Optional: true
  Description: An optional string for the initial prompt input.

Parameter: initialMessages
  Type: Messages[] = []
  Optional: true
  Description: An optional array of initial chat messages

Parameter: onToolCall
  Type: ({toolCall: ToolCall}) => void | unknown| Promise<unknown>
  Optional: true
  Description: Optional callback function that is invoked when a tool call is received. Intended for automatic client-side tool execution. You can optionally return a result for the tool call, either synchronously or asynchronously.

Parameter: onResponse
  Type: (response: Response) => void
  Optional: true
  Description: An optional callback that will be called with the response from the API endpoint. Useful for throwing customized errors or logging

Parameter: onFinish
  Type: (message: Message, options: OnFinishOptions) => void
  Optional: true
  Description: An optional callback function that is called when the completion stream ends.
  Properties:
    Type: OnFinishOptions
    Parameters:
      Parameter: usage
        Type: CompletionTokenUsage
        Optional: false
        Description: The token usage for the completion.
        Properties:
          Type: CompletionTokenUsage
          Parameters:
            Parameter: promptTokens
              Type: number
              Optional: false
              Description: The total number of tokens in the prompt.

            Parameter: completionTokens
              Type: number
              Optional: false
              Description: The total number of tokens in the completion.

            Parameter: totalTokens
              Type: number
              Optional: false
              Description: The total number of tokens generated.

      Parameter: finishReason
        Type: 'stop' | 'length' | 'content-filter' | 'tool-calls' | 'error' | 'other' | 'unknown'
        Optional: false
        Description: The reason why the generation ended.

Parameter: onError
  Type: (error: Error) => void
  Optional: true
  Description: A callback that will be called when the chat stream encounters an error. Optional.

Parameter: generateId
  Type: () => string
  Optional: true
  Description: A custom id generator for message ids and the chat id. Optional.

Parameter: headers
  Type: Record<string, string> | Headers
  Optional: true
  Description: Additional headers to be passed to the API endpoint. Optional.

Parameter: body
  Type: any
  Optional: true
  Description: Additional body object to be passed to the API endpoint. Optional.

Parameter: credentials
  Type: 'omit' | 'same-origin' | 'include'
  Optional: true
  Description: An optional literal that sets the mode of credentials to be used on the request. Defaults to same-origin.

Parameter: maxSteps
  Type: number
  Optional: true
  Description: Maximum number of backend calls to generate a response. A maximum number is required to prevent infinite loops in the case of misconfigured tools. By default, it is set to 1.

Parameter: streamProtocol
  Type: 'text' | 'data'
  Optional: true
  Description: An optional literal that sets the type of stream to be used. Defaults to `data`. If set to `text`, the stream will be treated as a text stream.

Parameter: fetch
  Type: FetchFunction
  Optional: true
  Description: 
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: AI SDK UI `useChat` Hook Reference
DESCRIPTION: API documentation for the `useChat` hook from the `@ai-sdk/vue` package. This hook simplifies the implementation of chat interfaces by providing state management for messages and utility functions for sending messages, typically interacting with a `/api/chat` endpoint by default.

SOURCE: https://github.com/vercel/ai/blob/main/content/docs/02-getting-started/05-nuxt.mdx#_snippet_10

LANGUAGE: APIDOC
CODE:
```
useChat(options?: object):
  messages: Array<{ id: string; role: string; parts: Array<{ type: string; text?: string }> }> (current chat messages)
  sendMessage(message: { text: string }): void (function to send a message to the chat API)
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Vercel AI SDK Chat Hook API Definition
DESCRIPTION: Defines the structure and functionality of the Vercel AI SDK's chat hook return object, including its properties and methods for chat management.

SOURCE: https://github.com/vercel/ai/blob/v5/content/docs/07-reference/02-ai-sdk-ui/01-use-chat.mdx#_snippet_8

LANGUAGE: APIDOC
CODE:
```
interface UseChatHookResult {
  error: Error | undefined;
  // An error object returned by SWR, if any.

  append: (message: Message | CreateMessage, options?: ChatRequestOptions) => Promise<string | undefined>;
  // Function to append a message to the chat, triggering an API call for the AI response.
  // It returns a promise that resolves to full response message content when the API call is successfully finished,
  // or throws an error when the API call fails.
  // Parameters:
  //   options (ChatRequestOptions):
  //     headers?: Record<string, string> | Headers;
  //       Additional headers that should be to be passed to the API endpoint.
  //     body?: object;
  //       Additional body JSON properties that should be sent to the API endpoint.
  //     data?: JSONValue;
  //       Additional data to be sent to the API endpoint.
  //     experimental_attachments?: FileList | Array<Attachment>;
  //       An array of attachments to be sent to the API endpoint.
  //       - FileList: A list of files that have been selected by the user using an <input type='file'> element.
  //                   It's also used for a list of files dropped into web content when using the drag and drop API.
  //       - Attachment: An attachment object that can be used to describe the metadata of the file.
  //         - name?: string;
  //           The name of the attachment, usually the file name.
  //         - contentType?: string;
  //           A string indicating the media type of the file.
  //         - url: string;
  //           The URL of the attachment. It can either be a URL to a hosted file or a Data URL.

  reload: (options?: ChatRequestOptions) => Promise<string | undefined>;
  // Function to reload the last AI chat response for the given chat history.
  // If the last message isn't from the assistant, it will request the API to generate a new response.
  // Parameters:
  //   options (ChatRequestOptions):
  //     headers?: Record<string, string> | Headers;
  //       Additional headers that should be to be passed to the API endpoint.
  //     body?: object;
  //       Additional body JSON properties that should be sent to the API endpoint.
  //     data?: JSONValue;
  //       Additional data to be sent to the API endpoint.

  stop: () => void;
  // Function to stop the ongoing AI response.
}
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: AI SDK UI: useChat Hook Enhancements
DESCRIPTION: Enhanced `useChat` with experimental support for attachments and streaming tool calls, providing more versatile chat functionalities. Patched to prevent empty submissions. `reload` function now correctly sends data, body, and headers. Added `onFinish` for token usage and finish reason.

SOURCE: https://github.com/vercel/ai/blob/main/content/docs/08-migration-guides/37-migration-guide-3-3.mdx#_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: APIDOC
CODE:
```
React Hook: useChat()
  - Attachments: Experimental support
  - Tool Calls: Experimental streaming support
  - Submissions: Prevents empty submissions
  - reload(): Fixes data, body, headers sending
  - onFinish: (usage: { completionTokens: number, promptTokens: number }, reason: string) => void (Access to token usage and finish reason)
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Remove options parameter from useChat hook
DESCRIPTION: The `options` parameter in the `useChat` hook has been removed. Instead, `headers` and `body` parameters should be used directly at the top level of the hook's configuration object.

SOURCE: https://github.com/vercel/ai/blob/v5/content/docs/08-migration-guides/29-migration-guide-4-0.mdx#_snippet_38

LANGUAGE: ts
CODE:
```
const { messages } = useChat({
  options: {
    headers: {
      'X-Custom-Header': 'value'
    }
  },
  // ...
});
```

LANGUAGE: ts
CODE:
```
const { messages } = useChat({
  headers: {
    'X-Custom-Header': 'value'
  },
  // ...
});
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Configuring useChat with DefaultChatTransport
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to configure the `useChat` hook in AI SDK 5 using a transport system, specifically `DefaultChatTransport`, to define API endpoints and request headers for chat interactions, enhancing modularity and state management.

SOURCE: https://github.com/vercel/ai/blob/v5/content/docs/01-announcing-ai-sdk-5-beta/index.mdx#_snippet_10

LANGUAGE: ts
CODE:
```
import { useChat } from '@ai-sdk/react';
import { DefaultChatTransport } from 'ai';

const { messages, sendMessage } = useChat({
  transport: new DefaultChatTransport({
    api: '/api/chat', // your chat endpoint
    headers: { 'Custom-Header': 'value' },
  }),
  maxSteps: 5,
});
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: AI SDK UI: useChat Hook
DESCRIPTION: The `useChat` hook from `@ai-sdk/react` simplifies building chat interfaces by managing chat state, user input, and API interactions. It defaults to using a POST API route at `/api/chat` for communication with the backend.

SOURCE: https://github.com/vercel/ai/blob/main/content/cookbook/00-guides/02-multi-modal-chatbot.mdx#_snippet_9

LANGUAGE: APIDOC
CODE:
```
useChat(): {
  messages: UIMessage[],
  input: string,
  handleInputChange: (event: React.ChangeEvent<HTMLInputElement>) => void,
  handleSubmit: (event: React.FormEvent<HTMLFormElement>) => void,
  status: string
}
  messages: An array of current chat messages, each with 'id', 'role', and 'content' properties.
  input: The current value of the user's input field.
  handleInputChange: A function to update the input field value based on user typing.
  handleSubmit: A function to handle form submission, triggering the chat API call.
  status: The current status of the API request (e.g., 'idle', 'loading', 'success', 'error').
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: AI SDK useChat Hook API Reference
DESCRIPTION: Details the `useChat` hook from `@ai-sdk/react`, explaining its purpose, state management, and default API endpoint. It enables streaming chat messages and automatic UI updates.

SOURCE: https://github.com/vercel/ai/blob/main/content/cookbook/00-guides/01-rag-chatbot.mdx#_snippet_17

LANGUAGE: APIDOC
CODE:
```
useChat(options: UseChatOptions): { messages: Message[], input: string, handleInputChange: (e: ChangeEvent<HTMLInputElement>) => void, handleSubmit: (e: FormEvent<HTMLFormElement>) => void }
  Description: Hook to easily create a conversational user interface. Enables streaming of chat messages, manages state for chat input, and updates UI automatically.
  Parameters:
    options: UseChatOptions - Configuration options for the chat hook.
      chatStore: ChatStoreOptions - Configuration for chat storage.
        api: string (default: '/api/chat') - The API endpoint to send chat messages to.
  Returns:
    messages: Message[] - Array of chat messages.
    input: string - Current value of the chat input field.
    handleInputChange: (e: ChangeEvent<HTMLInputElement>) => void - Event handler for input changes.
    handleSubmit: (e: FormEvent<HTMLFormElement>) => void - Event handler for form submission.
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Removed `streamMode` setting from `useChat` hook
DESCRIPTION: The `streamMode` option has been removed from the `useChat` hook's configuration. To control streaming behavior, developers should now use the `streamProtocol` parameter instead.

SOURCE: https://github.com/vercel/ai/blob/v5/content/docs/08-migration-guides/29-migration-guide-4-0.mdx#_snippet_36

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
const { messages } = useChat({
  streamMode: 'text',
  // ...
});
```

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
const { messages } = useChat({
  streamProtocol: 'text',
  // ...
});
```

