TITLE: AI SDK useChat Hook API Reference
DESCRIPTION: The `useChat` hook from `@ai-sdk/react` provides state and functions for building interactive chat interfaces. It manages message history, handles sending new messages, and integrates with a chat API endpoint.

SOURCE: https://github.com/vercel/ai/blob/main/content/docs/02-getting-started/07-expo.mdx#_snippet_8

LANGUAGE: APIDOC
CODE:
```
useChat Hook:
  - Parameters:
    - transport: DefaultChatTransport (required) - Configures how messages are sent and received.
      - fetch: Function (required) - Custom fetch implementation (e.g., expoFetch) for streaming.
      - api: string (required) - The API endpoint for chat communication.
    - onError: Function (optional) - Callback for handling errors during chat operations.
  - Returns: Object containing chat state and functions.
    - messages: Array<ChatMessage> - An array of current chat messages.
      - ChatMessage Object:
        - id: string - Unique identifier for the message.
        - role: string - Role of the message sender (e.g., 'user', 'assistant').
        - parts: Array<MessagePart> - Ordered array of content parts for the message.
          - MessagePart Object:
            - type: string - Type of the part (e.g., 'text').
            - text: string - The text content of the part (if type is 'text').
    - sendMessage: Function(message: { text: string }) - Sends a new message to the chat API.
      - Parameters:
        - message: Object
          - text: string - The text content of the message to send.
    - error: Error | undefined - An error object if an error occurred during chat operations.
```

