TITLE: AI SDK Tool Call Capabilities: Multi-Step Tool Calls
DESCRIPTION: This section details the handling of multi-step tool calls within the AI SDK. It explains the differences in implementation between AI SDK RSC, which requires a combination of streaming functions, and AI SDK UI's `useChat` hook, which offers built-in support with configurable `maxSteps`.

SOURCE: https://github.com/vercel/ai/blob/v5/content/docs/05-ai-sdk-rsc/10-migrating-to-ui.mdx#_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: APIDOC
CODE:
```
AI SDK RSC:
  - streamUI does not support multi-step tool calls.
  - Requires combination of streamText, createStreamableUI, and createStreamableValue.
AI SDK UI (useChat):
  - Built-in support for multi-step tool calls.
  - Set maxSteps in streamText function to define number of steps the language model can make in a single call.
  - useChat handles multi-step tool calls automatically.
```
